{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"09005a78-5c2c-4c87-8bdd-cb3db8156348","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_015CTMcBmU9BdGCsCE5HgYAr","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Configuring .NET crash dumps"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"e08e4f66-632a-40d1-977a-54a1e0047183","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` — enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` — dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` — path/pattern for the dump file\n\n\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` — points to the createdump tool location, which is critical for NativeAOT since it needs to know where to find `/opt/tools/createdump`\n\nThere are also some legacy variables like `COMPlus_DbgEnableMiniDump` from earlier .NET versions and `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics` for createdump diagnostics, but the main ones above should handle the configuration. Now I need to show how to set these in the Kubernetes pod spec.","outputTokens":342},"id":"ea0ca9f3-a0c2-4552-b0cc-8c178a02d41c","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:59:38.280Z","parentId":"f21e1229-8aeb-420e-9fca-e1783a030221"}
