{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8941cdf2-9760-46e5-899f-9f45962558f7","content":"Here are the pod spec changes for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      env:\n        # Enable automatic mini dump on crash\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        # Dump type: 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        # Path to createdump (required for NativeAOT — runtime can't discover it automatically)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%d.%t\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dump-volume\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dump-volume\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — critical for NativeAOT since the runtime won't auto-locate `createdump`.\n- **`%d` / `%t`** in the dump name expand to PID and timestamp, preventing overwrites on repeated crashes.\n- **Dump type 4 (Full)** gives the most diagnostic info; use `1` (Mini) or `3` (Triage) to save space.\n- The `emptyDir` volume ensures dumps survive container restarts within the pod. For persistence beyond pod lifetime, swap it for a PVC or ship dumps to external storage via a sidecar.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e08e4f66-632a-40d1-977a-54a1e0047183","outputTokens":423},"id":"cc5df53e-b410-404f-bafc-304dfd78bb44","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:59:46.597Z","parentId":"18e1e78c-387e-4182-8c14-61a7013c1774"}
